message.content:
There are several useful visual features to tell there is an apple pie in a photo:
- circular, pie-like shape
- golden-brown crust
- lattice or solid top crust 
- crimped or fluted edges
- visible apple filling or chunks
- a pie dish or plate
- often with a glossy, sugary surface
- potentially sliced, showing the layered interior

There are several useful visual features to tell there are baby back ribs in a photo:
- A rack of curved ribs
- Meaty portions between the bones
- Often glazed or coated with sauce
- Grilled or roasted appearance
- Charred or caramelized edges
- Served on a plate or platter
- Often accompanied by side dishes such as coleslaw, baked beans, or fries

- layered pastry dessert
- golden-brown color
- multiple thin layers of phyllo dough
- filled with chopped nuts (often pistachios, walnuts, or almonds)
- covered with syrup or honey, giving it a glistening appearance
- cut into diamond or square shapes
- occasionally topped with a sprinkle of crushed nuts

- thin slices of raw beef
- bright red or pink color of the meat
- arranged in a circular pattern or overlapping layers
- garnished with elements like arugula, capers, or shaved Parmesan cheese
- drizzled with olive oil or a similar dressing
- occasionally served with lemon wedges or a balsamic reduction
- presentation on a flat plate or platter

- raw ground or finely chopped beef
- typically reddish-pink in color
- often formed into a round or slightly flattened patty
- garnished with raw egg yolk on top or served on the side
- accompanied by capers, onions, and fresh herbs (e.g., parsley)
- may include seasonings such as mustard, Worcestershire sauce, or hot sauce
- presented on a plate, sometimes with toast or crackers

- vibrant red or purple beetroot pieces
- leafy greens (such as arugula or spinach)
- visible dressing or vinaigrette
- often garnished with cheese (such as goat cheese or feta)
- presence of nuts or seeds (such as walnuts or sunflower seeds)
- sometimes includes other vegetables (like carrots or cucumbers)
- can have a mix of textures (crunchy nuts, soft beets)
- possibly served in a bowl or on a plate

- small, square or rectangular shapes
- golden-brown, fried exterior 
- generous dusting of powdered sugar
- slightly puffy and airy texture
- can be served on a plate or in a basket
- often accompanied by coffee or other beverages

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a bibimbap in a photo:
- Korean dish
- a bowl of mixed rice
- various colorful vegetables (such as carrots, spinach, bean sprouts, and mushrooms)
- marinated meat (such as beef or chicken)
- a fried or raw egg on top
- gochujang sauce (red chili paste) often served on the side or mixed in
- sesame seeds or sesame oil
- sliced nori (seaweed) strips

- mixture of bread pieces and custard
- golden-brown or toasted top
- sometimes sprinkled with powdered sugar
- often cut into square or rectangular pieces
- occasionally garnished with raisins, nuts, or fruit
- served in a dish, often a baking pan
- a creamy or pudding-like interior texture
- may include a drizzle of sauce, such as caramel or vanilla sauce

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a breakfast burrito in a photo:
- cylindrical or rolled shape
- flour tortilla wrapping
- visible filling, often including scrambled eggs
- additional fillings like cheese, sausage, bacon, potatoes, peppers, or beans
- sometimes cut in half to show the internal ingredients
- often served on a plate or wrapped in foil/paper

- toasted or grilled bread slices
- topped with diced tomatoes
- garnished with fresh basil leaves
- drizzled with olive oil
- sprinkled with salt
- sometimes includes garlic
- may include toppings like cheese, prosciutto, or balsamic glaze

- green romaine lettuce
- croutons
- shaved or grated Parmesan cheese
- creamy dressing (often drizzled or tossed with the salad)
- sometimes includes slices of chicken, bacon, or anchovies
- prepared in a bowl or on a plate
- garnished with freshly cracked black pepper or lemon wedges

- cylindrical pastry shell, often golden brown
- filled with a creamy, white or off-white filling (usually ricotta cheese)
- typically dusted with powdered sugar on top
- sometimes ends are garnished with bits of chocolate, candied fruit, or pistachios
- might have a slight cracking texture on the pastry shell
- can be seen individually or in a grouped arrangement on a plate

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a caprese salad in a photo:
- Slices of tomatoes
- Slices of fresh mozzarella cheese
- Fresh basil leaves
- Drizzles of olive oil
- Drizzles or beads of balsamic vinegar (optional)
- Sprinkled salt and pepper
- Plate or serving dish (often arranged in an alternating pattern of tomato, mozzarella, and basil)

- orange or brownish color (due to grated carrots)
- visible carrot shreds or pieces within the cake
- a moist and dense texture
- layered or single-tiered structure
- a frosting layer, often cream cheese frosting 
- decorations on top, such as nuts or carrot-shaped icing
- round, square, or rectangular shape (commonly)
- can be decorated with additional ingredients like walnuts or raisins

- raw fish or seafood pieces
- bright colors (green, red, yellow) from vegetables like onions, tomatoes, and peppers
- citrus fruits (often lime or lemon) slices or wedges
- garnishes such as cilantro or parsley
- a liquid base or marinade that appears clear to slightly opaque, often with a tangy or acidic look
- served in a bowl or on a plate
- sometimes accompanied by side dishes like corn, sweet potato, or avocado

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a cheese plate in a photo:
- assortment of cheeses of various shapes and colors (blocks, slices, wedges)
- cutting board or serving platter
- accompaniments like crackers, bread, or breadsticks
- fruits such as grapes, apples, or berries
- nuts like almonds, walnuts, or cashews
- utensils such as cheese knives or spreaders
- possibly garnishes like herbs or honey
- an organized or artistic arrangement of items

- circular shape
- creamy, smooth texture
- light yellow or pale color
- crust, typically brown or golden, often made from graham crackers or cookies
- fruit, chocolate, or sauce topping (optional)
- layer separation, with a distinct crust layer at the bottom and a thicker creamy layer above
- garnish such as whipped cream, fruit slices, or chocolate shavings (optional)

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a chicken curry in a photo:
- chunks or pieces of chicken
- rich, gravy-like sauce
- vibrant colors such as yellow, orange, or red
- presence of spices or herbs like turmeric, coriander, or cumin
- vegetables like onions, tomatoes, or peppers (optional)
- garnished with fresh herbs like cilantro
- often served with rice or bread (like naan or roti)
- a bowl or plate with a serving of the curry

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a chicken quesadilla in a photo:
- folded or layered tortilla
- golden-brown, crispy exterior
- cheesy filling visible at the edges
- cooked chicken pieces inside
- may include additional fillings like bell peppers, onions, or seasonings
- often cut into triangular or wedge-shaped pieces
- served with sides like salsa, guacamole, or sour cream

There are several useful visual features to tell there are chicken wings in a photo:
- cooked or raw chicken parts
- usually small and elongated pieces
- bony structure visible
- crispy or fried outer texture for cooked wings
- seasoned or sauced exterior, often in orange, red, or brown for cooked wings
- skin-on or skin-off appearance
- joint sections, typically the drumette, wingette (flat), and tip
- served with dipping sauces or garnishes in many cooked presentations

- rich brown or dark color
- often covered in chocolate frosting, icing, or ganache
- round, square, or rectangular shape
- layers separated by frosting or filling
- decorated with chocolate shavings, sprinkles, or other confectionery
- sometimes topped with fruits, nuts, or additional chocolate pieces
- can have a glossy, smooth, or textured surface
- may be presented on a cake stand, plate, or in a baking dish

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a chocolate mousse in a photo:
- smooth, creamy texture
- rich, dark brown color
- served in a bowl, cup, or glass
- sometimes topped with whipped cream or chocolate shavings
- may have garnishes like mint leaves, berries, or nuts
- often presented in a visually appealing and elegant manner

There are several useful visual features to tell there are churros in a photo:
- elongated, cylindrical shape
- ridged or grooved surface
- golden-brown color
- dusting of sugar or cinnamon sugar
- sometimes served in small bites or lengths
- often accompanied by a dipping sauce (like chocolate or caramel)
- sometimes stacked or piled together
- might be found in a paper cone, tray, or on a plate

- creamy or broth-based soup
- typically white or light-colored (New England style) or red (Manhattan style)
- pieces of clam
- chunks of potatoes
- sometimes includes vegetables like celery and onions
- often garnished with parsley or oyster crackers
- served in a bowl or a bread bowl

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a club sandwich in a photo:
- multiple layers of bread
- slices of turkey or chicken
- bacon strips
- lettuce
- tomato slices
- mayonnaise or other condiments
- cut into quarters
- often held together by toothpicks
- visible cross-section showing all the layers

There are several useful visual features to tell there are crab cakes in a photo:
- circular or oval shape
- golden-brown crust
- varying textures with visible lump crab meat or other ingredients
- often served on a plate
- garnished with herbs or lemon wedges
- sometimes accompanied by dipping sauces or a side salad

- individual serving dish (often a ramekin)
- burnt or caramelized sugar crust on top
- smooth, creamy custard underneath the crust
- typically a pale yellow or cream-colored custard
- spoon for breaking the crust
- garnished with berries, mint leaves, or powdered sugar (occasionally)
- contrast between the glossy, hard caramelized top and the creamy texture of the custard

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a croque madame in a photo:
- sandwich or toast presentation
- fried or poached egg on top
- golden brown, crispy bread 
- melted cheese, often Gruyère or Emmental
- creamy béchamel sauce
- ham slices inside the sandwich
- possible garnish of herbs or greens

There are several useful visual features to tell there are cupcakes in a photo:
- individual, small cake servings
- typically presented in colorful paper or foil liners
- topped with frosting or icing
- often decorated with sprinkles, candies, or other edible decorations
- usually arranged on a tray, plate, or stand
- various flavors and colors
- fluffy or moist texture when the interior is visible

- Halved boiled eggs
- Creamy, yellow filling in the center of the egg white halves
- Garnished with paprika, herbs, or other seasonings
- Smooth or piped filling, often with a slightly lumpy texture
- White and yellow color contrast
- Often served on a platter or as finger food

- circular shape with a hole in the center or filled center
- glazed, frosted, powdered, or sprinkled on the surface
- golden-brown, pink, chocolate, or other vibrant colors
- doughy texture 
- often displayed in a box or on a tray
- toppings like nuts, sprinkles, or coconut shavings
- may be accompanied by coffee or milk

There are several useful visual features to tell there are dumplings in a photo:
- small, doughy parcels
- typically round, crescent-shaped, or pleated
- smooth or slightly textured surface
- often white, beige, or light brown
- may be steamed, boiled, fried, or baked
- sometimes have visible filling or crimped edges
- often accompanied by dipping sauces or in broth

There are several useful visual features to tell there is an edamame in a photo:
- young, green soybeans
- typically seen in their pods
- pods are bright green
- pods have a slightly fuzzy or hairy texture
- oval or slightly elongated shape
- often displayed in small clusters or groups
- beans inside the pods are also green and plump

There are several useful visual features to tell there are eggs benedict in a photo:
- English muffin halves
- Poached eggs
- Canadian bacon or ham slices
- Hollandaise sauce poured over the top
- Garnish, such as chopped chives or parsley
- Sometimes served with a side, like hash browns or a salad

There are several useful visual features to tell there are escargots (cooked snails) in a photo:
- Small, spiral shells
- Terrestrial appearance
- Cooked or served in a dish
- Typically presented in a tray with indentations
- Often accompanied by garlic butter or sauce
- May be garnished with parsley or herbs
- Textured, spiraled shell surface.

- round, ball or patty shape
- golden-brown, deep-fried exterior
- small to medium size (typically 2-3 inches in diameter)
- texture that appears crispy on the outside
- usually served with other ingredients like pita bread, salad, or sauce
- often accompanied by garnishes like tahini, pickles, or fresh vegetables
- may show a greenish interior, indicating the presence of herbs like parsley or cilantro

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a filet mignon in a photo:
- thick, cylindrical or oval-shaped cut of beef
- dark reddish-brown or pinkish color when raw
- often has a smooth and fine texture
- minimal visible fat or marbling
- sometimes wrapped in bacon (bacon-wrapped filet mignon)
- typically presented with minimal or no bone
- may be served with a seared, grilled, or broiled appearance when cooked
- often seen garnished or plated with sides like vegetables or sauces

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a fish and chips in a photo:
- golden-brown battered fish fillet
- crispy, golden-brown potato fries (chips)
- often served on a plate, tray, or wrapped in paper
- occasionally accompanied by lemon wedges
- tartar sauce, ketchup, or vinegar as potential condiments
- a side of peas or mushy peas may be present
- typically served in a casual dining setting

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a foie gras in a photo:
- creamy, smooth texture
- pale, beige to yellow color
- often presented in a slice or block form
- garnished with herbs, fruits, or sauce (optional)
- served on a plate or toast
- rich, glossy appearance
- typically accompanied by gourmet bread or crackers

- elongated pieces of fried potato
- golden-brown color
- crispy texture
- often served in a pile or container
- common accompaniment with condiments like ketchup or mayonnaise
- usually uniform in size and shape, but can vary depending on the cut (e.g., shoestring, crinkle-cut)
- sometimes seasoned with salt or other spices

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a French onion soup in a photo:
- rich, dark brown broth
- caramelized onions
- melted cheese on top, often browned or crispy
- usually served in a round, oven-safe bowl or crock
- a slice of toasted bread or crouton floating on top or just below the cheese
- possible garnishes like herbs (e.g., thyme or parsley)

There are several useful visual features to tell there is French toast in a photo:
- Sliced bread pieces 
- Golden-brown, crispy exterior
- Eggy and slightly custardy texture
- Sprinkles of powdered sugar
- Toppings such as fresh fruit, whipped cream, or syrup
- A plate or serving dish
- Often garnished with butter or a dusting of cinnamon

- golden-brown, crispy rings or tentacles
- often breaded or battered coating
- served on a plate or in a basket
- lemon wedges or slices often present
- may be served with dipping sauces, such as marinara or aioli
- garnished with parsley or other herbs
- can be accompanied by side items like fries or salad

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a fried rice in a photo:
- a mixture of cooked rice
- various small pieces of vegetables (like peas, carrots, and bell peppers)
- scrambled eggs mixed in
- small pieces of meat or seafood (commonly chicken, shrimp, or pork)
- soy sauce or other seasonings coating the rice
- a slightly oily or glossy appearance
- green garnishes, such as chopped scallions or cilantro

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a frozen yogurt in a photo:
- swirled or soft-serve texture
- served in a cup or cone
- toppings such as fruits, nuts, sprinkles, or syrups
- cold and creamy appearance
- pale colors or pastel shades
- often has a frosty or slightly glossy surface
- disposable spoons or utensils nearby

- baked bread, often sliced
- golden or toasted crust
- buttery texture
- visible pieces of garlic or garlic spread
- topped with herbs, commonly parsley
- sometimes cheese or additional ingredients sprinkled or melted on top
- typically served in a loaf, slices, or breadstick form

There are several useful visual features to tell there is gnocchi in a photo:
- small, round or oval-shaped pasta
- dumpling-like appearance
- smooth or ridged texture
- typically off-white, yellow, or beige color
- made from potato, flour, and eggs (ingredients might show in preparations)
- often served with sauce or melted butter
- may be garnished with herbs, cheese, or other toppings

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a Greek salad in a photo:
- a mix of fresh vegetables
- sliced cucumbers
- tomatoes, often cut into wedges
- green bell peppers, thinly sliced
- red onion rings
- Kalamata olives, usually whole or pitted
- cubes or slices of feta cheese
- sprinkled oregano
- a drizzle of olive oil
- no lettuce (traditional Greek salad does not include lettuce)

- golden-brown, toasted bread
- melted cheese oozing out between the slices of bread
- usually a sandwich cut in halves or quarters
- visible grill marks or a crispy texture on the bread surface
- a gooey or stringy appearance when the sandwich is pulled apart
- often served with a side, such as a pickle or tomato soup

- cooked fish
- pinkish-orange flesh
- grill marks (charred lines) on the surface
- flaky texture
- presence of skin (sometimes with visible scales)
- served on a plate or with side dishes like vegetables or lemon slices
- possible garnish such as herbs
- moist and slightly shiny appearance

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a guacamole in a photo:
- green, chunky or smooth texture
- typically in a bowl or on a plate
- presence of diced tomatoes, onions, or cilantro as garnishes
- may be accompanied by tortilla chips
- creamy consistency
- sprinkled with lime or avocado slices

- crescent-shaped dumpling
- pleated or crimped edge
- golden-brown or light brown on one side from pan-frying
- thin, slightly translucent dough
- small, usually about the size of a person's palm
- may have visible filling if the dough is partially open
- often served with dipping sauce on the side
- arranged in a group or in a circle on a plate

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a hamburger in a photo:
- round, typically bun-like pieces of bread
- a cooked ground meat patty (usually beef)
- leafy green lettuce 
- slices of tomato 
- yellow or white cheese (often melted)
- pickles or onions
- condiments like ketchup or mustard
- sometimes bacon or additional toppings

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a hot and sour soup in a photo:
- brown or dark broth
- tofu pieces
- mushrooms (often wood ear or shiitake)
- bamboo shoots
- egg ribbons or swirls
- pieces of meat (often pork or chicken)
- colorful garnishes like green onions or cilantro
- a steaming, hot appearance
- sometimes served in a bowl with a spoon

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a hot dog in a photo:
- elongated sausage or frankfurter
- positioned inside a sliced bread roll, bun, or similar enclosure
- brown, reddish, or pinkish hue of the sausage
- toppings such as mustard, ketchup, relish, onions, or sauerkraut
- potential presence of grill marks
- typically garnished with various condiments and sometimes vegetables
- often served in a paper or plastic tray or wrap

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a huevos rancheros in a photo:
- eggs, usually fried or sunny-side up
- tortillas, often corn tortillas, as a base
- tomato-based sauce or salsa, often with onions and chili peppers
- refried beans or black beans
- garnishes like avocado slices or guacamole
- often topped with fresh cilantro
- sometimes accompanied by rice
- possible addition of cheese, such as queso fresco or cheddar

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a hummus in a photo:
- creamy, beige or light tan color
- smooth, thick texture
- often served in a bowl or plate
- topped with olive oil drizzle
- sometimes garnished with paprika, chopped parsley, or whole chickpeas
- surrounded by accompanying foods like pita bread, carrots, or celery sticks
- presence of chickpeas and other Mediterranean/Middle Eastern foods nearby

- creamy, smooth texture
- served in a bowl, cone, or on a stick
- often in scoops or swirls
- various colors depending on flavor (white, pink, brown, etc.)
- may have toppings such as sprinkles, nuts, or syrups
- can be melting if exposed to warmth
- typically has a cold, frosty appearance
- can be seen with a spoon or other utensil nearby

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a lasagna in a photo:
- layered structure
- visible pasta sheets
- rich tomato sauce or meat sauce layers
- creamy béchamel or ricotta cheese layers
- melted, bubbly cheese on top
- typically served in rectangular or square pieces
- often seen in a baking dish or on a plate

- creamy, smooth texture
- typically orange, reddish, or pink in color
- served in a bowl or soup cup
- garnished with lobster meat or herbs
- often accompanied by bread or crackers
- presence of a rich, thick liquid consistency
- may have a drizzle of cream or a swirl pattern on top

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a lobster roll sandwich in a photo:
- a split-top or side-opened bun, often toasted
- chunky lobster meat, typically in sizeable pieces
- a creamy or buttery dressing, often mayonnaise-based
- garnishes such as chopped celery or lettuce
- sometimes sprinkled with herbs like chives or parsley
- the presence of side items like fries or coleslaw
- bright colors, primarily red for lobster and golden brown for the bun

- pasta, typically elbow macaroni
- creamy or cheesy sauce
- yellow-orange color
- often served in a bowl or on a plate
- may have breadcrumb topping
- might be garnished with herbs or additional cheese
- can be baked, so could have a golden-brown crust on top

- small, round, and sandwich-like shape
- smooth, domed tops
- flat bottoms
- vibrant and varied colors
- creamy or ganache-like filling between two cookie halves
- often presented in rows or stacked
- typically about the size of a coin

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a miso soup in a photo:
- light to medium brown broth
- often served in a small bowl
- presence of tofu cubes
- green onions or scallions
- seaweed pieces (such as wakame)
- sometimes floating mushrooms or other vegetables
- a small spoon or chopsticks nearby

There are several useful visual features to tell there are mussels in a photo:
- Bivalve mollusks with two shells
- Oval or elongated shape
- Smooth, dark-colored shells, often black, blue, or brown
- Shiny and slightly iridescent exterior
- Visible growth lines or ridges on the shells
- Small, hinged opening between the shells
- Presence of byssal threads (hair-like fibers) sometimes visible
- Often found in clusters or attached to rocks, piers, or other surfaces

- Tortilla chips
- Melted cheese
- Often topped with jalapeños
- Frequently garnished with sour cream, guacamole, salsa, or diced tomatoes
- Sometimes includes beans, ground meat, or chicken
- Layered or scattered presentation on a plate or platter
- Colorful due to the variety of toppings
- Often served as a casual meal or snack

There are several useful visual features to tell there is an omelette in a photo:
- cooked egg mixture, typically yellow or golden-brown in color
- round or folded shape
- smooth or slightly textured surface
- often garnished with herbs, vegetables, cheese, or meats
- may be served on a plate
- often seen accompanied by breakfast items like toast, bacon, or hash browns

There are several useful visual features to tell there are onion rings in a photo:
- Circular, ring-shaped food items
- Golden-brown, crispy exterior
- Layers of translucent onion visible within the batter
- Irregular, uniform size
- Often served in a pile or on a plate
- Frequently accompanied by dipping sauces
- Texture appears crunchy or fried

There are several useful visual features to tell there are oysters in a photo:
- hard, irregularly shaped shells
- rough and textured exterior
- colors ranging from grey to brown, with occasional hints of white or cream
- a fluted or bumpy surface on the shell
- slightly open shells showing the soft, fleshy interior
- clustered arrangement, often found in groups
- sometimes found on rocks or in shallow water
- occasional presence of barnacles or seaweed attached to shells

- Stir-fried noodles
- Brownish color due to sauces
- Garnished with crushed peanuts
- Lime wedge on the side
- Bean sprouts
- Chopped green onions
- Scrambled egg pieces
- Protein options like shrimp, chicken, or tofu
- Often served with a wedge of lime and sometimes fresh cilantro
- Visible tamarind paste or sauce mix

- large, shallow pan (traditionally wide and round)
- a base of yellow rice (colored by saffron)
- visible pieces of seafood such as shrimp, mussels, and clams
- chunks of meat, like chicken or rabbit
- a mix of colorful vegetables such as bell peppers, peas, and tomatoes
- garnished with lemon wedges
- often seen with a slightly golden, crispy bottom layer (socarrat)

There are several useful visual features to tell there are pancakes in a photo:
- circular and flat shape
- golden-brown color on the surface
- stacked one on top of another
- slightly fluffy or airy texture
- may be topped with butter, syrup, or other toppings
- often accompanied by sides like fruits or whipped cream
- may see a fork, knife, or plate used for serving

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a panna cotta in a photo:
- creamy, smooth texture
- typically white or pale color
- molded into a dome or cup shape
- often served with a fruit sauce or coulis on top or around
- garnished with fresh fruits, berries, or mint leaves
- may be decorated with a dusting of powdered sugar or a drizzle of caramel sauce
- usually presented on a small plate or in a shallow dish

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a Peking duck in a photo:
- White plumage
- Orange bill
- Orange legs and webbed feet
- Rounded body shape
- Relatively short neck
- Upright posture
- Presence in a farm or domestic setting (since Peking ducks are typically kept for meat and eggs)

Note that if you’re distinguishing the dish "Peking duck" rather than the bird, the following features would be relevant:
- Cooked, glazed duck with crispy skin
- Often presented whole or in slices
- Served alongside thin pancakes or steamed buns
- Accompanied by hoisin sauce
- Garnished with sliced cucumbers and green onions

There are several useful visual features to tell there is pho in a photo:
- a bowl
- broth, typically clear and light-colored
- rice noodles, usually thin and white
- slices of meat, such as beef or chicken
- fresh herbs, often including basil, cilantro, and scallions
- lime wedge or slices
- bean sprouts
- chili peppers
- a side dish with hoisin sauce and Sriracha or other hot sauce

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a pizza in a photo:
- circular or sometimes rectangular shape
- flatbread base
- distinctive crust around the edges
- layer of melted cheese, often covering the entire top
- visible tomato sauce, usually red
- various toppings such as pepperoni, vegetables, and meats
- slices, commonly triangular and radiating out from the center
- often seen in a pizza box, on a tray, or on a pizza peel

- slice of meat
- typically pinkish-red in color before cooking
- may have a visible bone, often a rib bone
- marbling of fat within the meat
- a layer of fat around the edge
- often has a symmetrical, oval or oblong shape
- sometimes seasoned or cooked, which may alter the color to brown or golden
- grill marks or sear marks if cooked

There are several useful visual features to tell there is poutine in a photo:
- a base of french fries
- topped with cheese curds
- covered in brown gravy
- often served in a bowl or on a plate
- looks greasy or saucy
- may include additional toppings like meats or herbs, but not always

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a prime rib in a photo:
- Large cut of beef
- Bone-in or boneless rib section
- Marbled with fat throughout the meat
- Brown, crispy crust if cooked
- Pink to red interior if cooked rare to medium (colors may vary with doneness)
- Often served with ribs portion visible
- Juicy appearance, sometimes shown with juices or au jus

- shredded or stringy pieces of slow-cooked pork
- sauce, often BBQ, coating the pork
- a bun or bread (often a hamburger-style bun)
- sometimes additional toppings like coleslaw, pickles, or onions
- a slightly messy and juicy appearance
- occasionally a side of fries, coleslaw, or a serving plate

- bowl of noodles
- broth (can be clear, creamy, or dark)
- sliced meat (such as pork or chicken)
- boiled or soft-boiled egg
- chopped green onions
- nori (seaweed) sheets
- bamboo shoots
- colorful and varied toppings (such as corn, mushrooms, or sprouts)
- chopsticks or a spoon alongside or in the bowl

There are several useful visual features to tell there is a ravioli in a photo:
- square or circular pasta pockets
- crimped or sealed edges
- filling inside (usually visible from a slight puffiness)
- typically served with a sauce or broth
- pale yellow or golden color (uncooked) or varying shades depending on the filling and sauce (cooked)
- sometimes speckled with herbs or seasoning
- appearance of pasta texture (smooth to slightly rough)

- vibrant red or reddish-brown interior
- layered cake structure
- white or cream-colored frosting, often cream cheese frosting
- decorative toppings, such as sprinkles or cake crumbs, often matching the red color
